@*
============================================================================
_Imports.razor

Purpose: Global using statements for all Blazor components
These namespaces are automatically available in all .razor files
without needing explicit @using directives in each file

Benefits:
- Reduces boilerplate in component files
- Ensures consistency across all components
- Centralized namespace management
============================================================================
*@

@* Routing components: Router, NavLink, etc. *@
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Routing

@* Core Blazor web components: EventCallback, RenderFragment, etc. *@
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web

@* Render mode directives: InteractiveServer, InteractiveAuto, etc. *@
@using static Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web.RenderMode

@* JavaScript interop: IJSRuntime for calling JS from C# *@
@using Microsoft.JSInterop

@* Root namespace: Access to Program, Services, etc. *@
@using WeatherDashboard

@* Components namespace: Access to shared components, layouts, pages *@
@using WeatherDashboard.Components
